      "message": "Now I\u0027m confused. Why use PacketLineIn? When I call Github on a repository that I cannot access, I get the following:\n```\n$ curl -v -H \u0027Accept: application/x-git-upload-pack-advertisement\u0027 https://github.com/some/privaterepo.git/info/refs?service\u003dgit-upload-pack\n* Host github.com:443 was resolved.\n* IPv6: (none)\n* IPv4: 140.82.121.3\n*   Trying 140.82.121.3:443...\n* schannel: disabled automatic use of client certificate\n* ALPN: curl offers http/1.1\n* ALPN: server accepted http/1.1\n* Connected to github.com (140.82.121.3) port 443\n* using HTTP/1.x\n\u003e GET /some/privaterepo.git/info/refs?service\u003dgit-upload-pack HTTP/1.1\n\u003e Host: github.com\n\u003e User-Agent: curl/8.14.1\n\u003e Accept: application/x-git-upload-pack-advertisement\n\u003e\n* Request completely sent off\n* schannel: remote party requests renegotiation\n* schannel: renegotiating SSL/TLS connection\n* schannel: SSL/TLS connection renegotiated\n* schannel: remote party requests renegotiation\n* schannel: renegotiating SSL/TLS connection\n* schannel: SSL/TLS connection renegotiated\n\u003c HTTP/1.1 401 Unauthorized\n\u003c Server: GitHub-Babel/3.0\n\u003c Content-Security-Policy: default-src \u0027none\u0027; sandbox\n\u003c Content-Type: text/plain; charset\u003dUTF-8\n\u003c www-authenticate: Basic realm\u003d\"GitHub\"\n\u003c Content-Length: 21\n\u003c Date: Mon, 11 May 2026 11:50:42 GMT\n\u003c X-Frame-Options: DENY\n\u003c Strict-Transport-Security: max-age\u003d31536000; includeSubDomains; preload\n\u003c X-GitHub-Request-Id: ...\n\u003c\nRepository not found.* Connection #0 to host github.com left intact\n$\n```\nSo I get an HTTP 401 with a text/plain body \"Repository not found.\" (no line feed at the end). Note that I get text/plain even though I specified I\u0027d accept only application/x-git-upload-pack-advertisement.\n\nParsing \"Repository not found\" with PacketLineIn is not going to work.\n\nTrying a dumb request:\n```\n$ curl -v -H \u0027Accept: */*\u0027 https://github.com/some/privaterepo.git/info/refs\n* Host github.com:443 was resolved.\n* IPv6: (none)\n* IPv4: 140.82.121.3\n*   Trying 140.82.121.3:443...\n* schannel: disabled automatic use of client certificate\n* ALPN: curl offers http/1.1\n* ALPN: server accepted http/1.1\n* Connected to github.com (140.82.121.3) port 443\n* using HTTP/1.x\n\u003e GET /some/privaterepo.git/info/refs HTTP/1.1\n\u003e Host: github.com\n\u003e User-Agent: curl/8.14.1\n\u003e Accept: */*\n\u003e\n* Request completely sent off\n* schannel: remote party requests renegotiation\n* schannel: renegotiating SSL/TLS connection\n* schannel: SSL/TLS connection renegotiated\n* schannel: remote party requests renegotiation\n* schannel: renegotiating SSL/TLS connection\n* schannel: SSL/TLS connection renegotiated\n* schannel: server close notification received (close_notify)\n\u003c HTTP/1.1 403 Forbidden\n\u003c Cache-Control: no-cache\n\u003c Content-Type: text/plain\n\u003c Strict-Transport-Security: max-age\u003d31536000; includeSubDomains; preload\n\u003c connection: close\n\u003c\nPlease upgrade your git client.\nGitHub.com no longer supports git over dumb-http: https://github.com/blog/809-git-dumb-http-transport-to-be-turned-off-in-90-days\n* schannel: server indicated shutdown in a prior call\n* shutting down connection #0\n```\n(Replace \"some/privaterepo.git\" with some really existing repo you don\u0027t have public access to).",
